    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": false,
    "title": "handle InitData() failures in optimistic compact block reconstruction",
    "user": {
      "login": "mjthecoder65",
      "id": 66741529,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY2NzQxNTI5",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/66741529?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/mjthecoder65",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mjthecoder65/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "Summary:\r\nIn the optimistic compact block reconstruction path (entered when the block\r\nis already in-flight from a different peer, or this peer has too many blocks\r\noutstanding), `InitData()` failures were silently ignored behind a`// TODO: don't ignore failures\\` comment.\r\n\r\nThis commit resolves the TODO by distinguishing between the two failure\r\nmodes, consistent with the handling in the non-optimistic path above\r\n(~L4594) and in `ProcessCompactBlockTxns` (~L3487):\r\n\r\n- `READ_STATUS_INVALID`: the compact block is malformed. For example an invalid header or data the peer constructed intentionally). Call `Misbehaving()`\r\n  on the peer. No `RemoveBlockRequest` is needed here because\r\n  `BlockRequested` was never called for this peer in the optimistic path.\r\n- `READ_STATUS_FAILED`: likely a short-id hash collision — not the peer's\r\n  fault. Return silently as before.",
    "labels": [
      {
        "id": 98298007,
